message.content:
cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper explores the security and privacy considerations of the decentralised web powered by Project Maelstrom. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the browser uses a distributed peer-to-peer network to host websites. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the protocol used by Project Maelstrom and its impact on website distribution. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) could be a possible category as the paper explores the new visitor-powered web-hosting paradigm and its implications for website development. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the censorship implications of the decentralised web and its impact on information networks.
